Subject: Re: [T2] Can I run 2L engine without od covers, (bottom tin)

On Fri, 4 Nov 2005, Courtney Hook wrote:

> Just wondering if I can run the engine for about 20 minutes without the
> bottom tin that protects the pushrods? It goes between the heat exchangers
> and the engine bottom? I want to check for pushrod tube leakage and other
> possible leak areas?

you must have the tin ABOVE the pushrods between the cyls but I've been
running mine without any lower tin for over 8 years and about 75k, I don't
have heat exchangers down there either.

YMMV

